Appwrite is an open-source backend-as-a-service (BaaS) platform that provides developers with a set of tools and APIs to manage various backend services like authentication, databases, file storage, cloud functions, and more. It is designed to simplify the development process by offering a self-hosted solution for creating full-stack applications without needing to manage your own backend infrastructure.

Key Features of Appwrite:
Authentication: Provides user authentication via email, OAuth, or anonymous logins.
Database: A document-based database that supports queries and permissions.
Storage: Handles file uploads and storage management.
Realtime: Real-time data updates via subscriptions to changes.
Cloud Functions: Allows the execution of server-side code (functions) that respond to specific events.



